[Student "S"]
{South's 1NT opening shows 15-17 points. What is your bid? 

With 11 points you are strong enough to force to game. With a 5-card \S suit you should transfer partner to \Ss by bidding 2\H. Partner dutifully responds 2\S.  

You must make a bid that will force partner to game, but at the same time inform him that you have only 5 \Ss (remember, your transfer promised <b>AT LEAST</b> 5). The bid that says both of these facts at once is 3NT. Partner comes back with 4\S. What say you? 

You say pass.

You might revalue your hand up to 12 points now that an 8-card fit has been discovered, but with partner's maximum of 17 you are nowhere near slam range.

A 4\S contract is definitely the place to be. }

